  "prompt": "What should I do to get selected in GSOC 2018?",
  "response": "To increase your chances of being selected for Google Summer of Code (GSoC) 2018, here are some key steps:\n\n1. Preparation\n- Choose an organization that matches your skills and interests\n- Learn about the organization's technology stack\n- Familiarize yourself with their contribution process\n- Start contributing to open-source projects early\n\n2. Technical Skills\n- Have strong programming skills\n- Be proficient in relevant programming languages\n- Understand version control (Git)\n- Have basic knowledge of software development practices\n\n3. Project Proposal\n- Research the organization's project ideas\n- Develop a detailed, well-structured project proposal\n- Include:\n  - Project objectives\n  - Detailed implementation plan\n  - Timeline\n  - Potential challenges and solutions\n- Show technical depth and understanding\n- Demonstrate your passion for the project\n\n4. Contributions\n- Make meaningful contributions to the organization\n- Submit patches or fix small bugs\n- Engage with the community on mailing lists/forums\n- Show communication and collaboration skills\n\n5. Application Process\n- Follow GSoC application guidelines\n- Submit a compelling proposal\n- Have your proposal reviewed by mentors\n- Be responsive and professional\n\n6. Communication\n- Actively communicate with mentors\n- Ask clarifying questions\n- Show enthusiasm and commitment\n\n7. Additional Tips\n- Start early\n- Be persistent\n- Learn from previous years' proposals\n- Build a strong GitHub profile",
